==English==
===Etymology===
From Middle English < Old English '''[[toþ|tōþ]]''' (''plural:'' '''teþ''') < Proto-Germanic '''*tanth''' / '''*tunth''' < Proto-Indo-European '''[[*dont-]]'''/'''[[*dent-]]''' (tooth).

===Noun===
'''tooth''' (''plural:'' '''teeth''')

#A hard, [[calcareous]] structure present in the [[mouth]] of many [[vertebrate]] [[animals]], generally used for [[eat]]ing.
#A sharp [[projection]] on a [[saw]] or similar implement.
#A [[projection]] on the edge of a [[gear]] that meshes with the teeth of adjacent gears or on the [[circumference]] of a [[cog]] that engages with a [[chain]].

